
## OpenSSH server setup 
- Installed 'openssh-server' using 'sudo apt install openssh-server -y'
- Verified ssh is active 'systemctl status ssh'
- Found VM IP address using 'ip a'
- Troubleshooted VM network connection; switched to bridged networking
- Sucessfully connected from host using 'ssh user@ip'
- Safely shut down Ubuntu vm with bash 


## Commands
- 'sudo systemctl status ssh'
- 'sudo systemctl enable ssh'
- 'sudo systemctl start ssh'
- 'ip a'
- 'sudo shutdown -c'
- 'sudo shutdown -h +1'

